  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to assess the outcomes of breast conserving therapy operation
      depending on the type of surgical tool used: classic electrocoagulation with higher operative
      temperatures and high frequency electrocoagulation with lower operative temperatures. The
      investigators would assess the pain levels, length and amount of the lymphatic secretion as
      well as quality of life following breast conserving surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
